component.name: camel-dap-server
component.description: Debug Adapter for Apache Camel based on Debug Adapter Protocol

components.name: org.eclipse.lsp4j.debug
components.description: Java bindings for the Debug Server Protocol

components.name: error_prone_annotations
components.description: Error Prone is a static analysis tool for Java that catches common programming mistakes at compile-time.

components.name: log4j-slf4j-impl
components.description: SLF4J 1 binding (provider) for the Log4j API. It forwards SLF4J 1 calls to the Log4j API. (Refer to the `log4j-to-slf4j` artifact for forwarding the Log4j API to SLF4J.)

components.name: log4j-api
components.description: The logging API of the Log4j project. Library and application code can log through this API. It contains a simple built-in implementation (`SimpleLogger`) for trivial use cases. Production applications are recommended to use Log4j API in combination with a fully-fledged implementation, such as Log4j Core.

components.name: log4j-core
components.description: A versatile, industrial-grade, and reference implementation of the Log4j API. It bundles a rich set of components to assist various use cases: Appenders targeting files, network sockets, databases, SMTP servers; Layouts that can render CSV, HTML, JSON, Syslog, etc. formatted outputs; Filters that can be configured using log event rates, regular expressions, scripts, time, etc. It contains several extension points to introduce custom components, if needed.

components.name: jaxb-impl
components.description: Old JAXB Runtime module. Contains sources required for runtime processing.

components.name: jaxb-core
components.description: Old JAXB Core module. Contains sources required by XJC, JXC and Runtime modules with dependencies.

components.name: commons-logging
components.description: Apache Commons Logging is a thin adapter allowing configurable bridging to other, well known logging systems.

components.name: commons-codec
components.description: The Apache Commons Codec component contains encoders and decoders for various formats such as Base16, Base32, Base64, digest, and Hexadecimal. In addition to these widely used encoders and decoders, the codec package also maintains a collection of phonetic encoding utilities.
